auth0:index/attackProtection:AttackProte.description:
Auth0 can detect attacks and stop malicious attempts to access your application such as blocking traffic from certain IPs and displaying CAPTCHAs.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as auth0 from "@pulumi/auth0";

const myProtection = new auth0.AttackProtection("myProtection", {
    breachedPasswordDetection: {
        adminNotificationFrequencies: ["daily"],
        enabled: true,
        method: "standard",
        preUserRegistration: {
            shields: ["block"],
        },
        shields: [
            "admin_notification",
            "block",
        ],
    },
    bruteForceProtection: {
        allowlists: ["127.0.0.1"],
        enabled: true,
        maxAttempts: 5,
        mode: "count_per_identifier_and_ip",
        shields: [
            "block",
            "user_notification",
        ],
    },
    suspiciousIpThrottling: {
        allowlists: ["192.168.1.1"],
        enabled: true,
        preLogin: {
            maxAttempts: 100,
            rate: 864000,
        },
        preUserRegistration: {
            maxAttempts: 50,
            rate: 1200,
        },
        shields: [
            "admin_notification",
            "block",
        ],
    },
});
```
